==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bloodroot
<hw>Blood"root`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant (<spn>Sanguinaria Canadensis</spn>), with a red root and
red sap, and bearing a pretty, white flower in early spring; -- called
also <altname>puccoon</altname>, <altname>redroot</altname>,
<altname>bloodwort</altname>, <altname>tetterwort</altname>,
<altname>turmeric</altname>, and <altname>Indian paint</altname>. It has
acrid emetic properties, and the rootstock is used as a stimulant
expectorant. See <er>Sanguinaria</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In England the name is given to the tormentil, once used
as a remedy for dysentery.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bloodshed</ent>⟦br⟧
